    id: 11,
    title: "what is a combination skin and how you can cure it?",
    image: "./blogs/what-is-a-combination-skin-and-how-you-can-cure-it.jpg",
    slug: "what-is-a-combination-skin-and-how-you-can-cure-it",
    intro: "Combination skin might be challenging to take care of, but it is not impossible. To properly care for mixed skin, you must discover products that are effective on the various skin types present on your face and do not irritate it.",
    content: "You can care by using these natural remedies:<br/><br/>1. Maintain a regular skin-care routine: Developing a daily and nightly skin care routine is essential for managing mixed skin. To help your skin adjust to the regimen, use the same products 1-2 times a day for at least a month.<br/>• Use a cleanser to wash your face once or twice every day. <br/>• Exfoliate seldom, occasionally just once each week. <br/>• Use a moisturiser to seal the deal every morning and night.<br/><br/>2. Consider treating various facial regions: You will need to concentrate on treating two skin types with this skin type. You must moisturise the dry parts of your face and cut back on the extra oil on the oily parts. Your T-zone is frequently the greasy region of your face (your forehead, nose, above your mouth, and chin). <br/>Depending on your skin type, you will need to treat particular sections of your face as opposed to your entire face with one product. Use a spot treatment to target the oil only on your forehead, for instance, if you have a breakout on your forehead and are aware that this area is prone to oiliness. Use a moisturising product exclusively on the area of your cheeks where your skin is prone to becoming dry and irritated. <br/><br/>3. On dry skin, use an oil-based cleanser: Coconut oil and olive oil- based cleansers are excellent for dry to very dry skin and may only be effective on the dry patches of combination skin. Although oil-based cleansers are not harmful to your skin, oily skin is not advised to use them. For a test period, you might want to try preparing a variety of various oil-based cleansers. Use a professional cleanser that has additional substances to more effectively treat oily skin if you begin to break out or experience adverse reactions. <br/><br/>4. A natural exfoliant can be made: After washing your face, you can exfoliate your skin to remove dead skin cells, especially if there are any dry or dead skin cell-filled areas of your face. Exfoliating will help stop pores from getting clogged and skin from looking lifeless. Once or twice a week, begin by exfoliating with a homemade scrub. <br/><br/>5. Use a natural spot remedy: Use spot treatments to get rid of blemishes and stop new acne from developing in your T-zone. By doing so, you will be able to focus on your face's acne-prone areas while avoiding bothering other areas. <br/><br/>6. Use organic face wash: Once a week, use a face mask to offer your skin a soothing treatment and a fresher complexion. Several organic, all- natural face masks combine oils and fruits to create a fantastic paste for your face. • Blend together two carrots, a banana, half a papaya, and a cup of honey. The ingredients should be combined to create a thick paste. For 20 minutes, apply this paste to your face. After that, wash it off with warm water. <br/>• One tablespoon of natural yoghurt, one teaspoon of lemon juice, and two drops of lemon essential oil can be used to make a lemon yoghurt face mask. Spend ten minutes covering your face with the mask. After that, remove it with warm water. <br/><br/>This is how you can take care of your combination skin but in case you face any problem you should talk to your dermatologist."
