    slug: "remedies-to-cure-hair-loss",
    intro: "Everyday hair loss is perfectly normal. However, it can be challenging to identify the cause of significant hair loss, especially in women. Minor hair loss is typically just your body's way of replacing the damaged hair with new, healthy ones. It's very normal to lose approximately 100 hairs per day. It's a fantastic idea to merely observe what you generally see in your brush or shower drain if you're unsure of what is common for you.",
    content: "<b>What causes Hair Loss?</b> <br/>If you've noticed your hair is thinning, falling out more frequently than usual, or growing more slowly, Here are some of the most common causes of hair loss you must be aware of: <br/><br/>Hereditary: A hereditary disorder that develops with ageing is the most frequent cause of hair loss. Androgenic alopecia, male-pattern baldness, and female-pattern baldness are the names for this disorder. It typically happens gradually and in regular patterns, with men experiencing a receding hairline and bald spots and women experiencing thinning hair at the top of the head. <br/><br/>Medications and supplements: Drugs for conditions like cancer, arthritis, depression, heart issues, gout, and high blood pressure may cause hair loss as a side effect. <br/><br/>Stressful event: Several months after a physical or mental shock, many persons notice a general thinning of their hair. Temporary hair loss results from this type. <br/><br/>Hairstyles and treatments: Excessive styling or tight-pulling hairstyles, like pigtails or cornrows, can result in traction alopecia, a kind of hair loss. Permanent hair dye and hot oil treatments can both make hair brittle and fall out. Scarring could cause hair loss to become permanent. Home cures for thinning hair: <br/><br/>Coconut Spa: Coconut oil (nariyal ka tel), one of the most effective home remedies for hair loss, is a favourite of mothers and grandmothers in India. The fatty acids in the oil fortify your hair roots and vigorously encourage hair development. <br/><br/>How to Stop Hair Fall Using Coconut Oil: <br/>• Apply a few teaspoons of warm coconut oil to your scalp. <br/>• Gently massage the scalp and let it sit overnight (or leave on for 20 minutes during the day) <br/>• The next morning, rinse with a gentle wash (or on the same day) <br/>Note: Frequency should be twice per week <br/><br/>Amla & Lime Juice Hair Pack to Stop Hair Loss: Amla, also known as the Indian Gooseberry, is a potent ayurvedic treatment that can strengthen your hair and delay hair ageing. Amla, which is rich in vitamin C, accelerates unrivalled hair growth. <br/>• To form a thick paste, combine 1 teaspoon of amla powder with a few drops of lime juice. <br/>• 40 minutes after applying the paste on your scalp. <br/>• Utilize a gentle cleaner to rinse the paste. <br/>Note: Apply the paste once or twice a week  <br/><br/>These are the methods by which you can thicken your hair and manage your hairfall at home.",
