    content: "<b>The Perfect Body: </b> We have various types of body looks as a human.  <br/>The first one is called“Ectomorph,” where the body weight is usually way below the average weight of their height. They usually have a fast metabolism and eat nonstop without gaining weight. It is beneficial for women, thanks to the growing craze for a slim body. But the downside is if you are too thin, people judge you for being a smoker, alcoholic, anti-social, or someone who lacks leadership qualities. <br/>Another body type is Endomorph, which is completely opposite to the above one. These are people with a lot of body fat. They struggle to lose weight despite following a variety of diet plans and exercise routines. <br/>The final one is mesomorphic people. They can easily gain muscle while maintaining a lean, desirable physique. A mesomorph is neither overweight nor underweight. They have the large frame of an endomorph but the low body fat of an ectomorph. <br/><br/><b>Breasts and Buttocks: Where Should Your Fat Go, For The Perfect Look?</b> <br/><br/>Breasts: Research shows that people find thin women with huge breasts to be more appealing, attractive, and healthy. Compared to women with other body types, women with large breasts and a thin waist have higher levels of female hormones. <br/>Thus, a woman with the fashionable 36-24-36 figure will have huge breasts but a slim waist. Achieving this weight can lower your risk of developing endometrial cancer, monthly irregularities, hirsutism, or excessive hair, high plasma triglycerides, diabetes, hypertension, heart attacks, and strokes. <br/><br/>Butts: Keeping your waistline in check might be difficult. Women’s bodies vary a lot throughout their lives. Hormonal fluctuations may cause your belly fat to migrate from your thighs and hips. This is clear from the fact that most women gain a lot of bellies fat after giving birth. A small waist is simple to attain. You must include oblique-focused activities in your workout plan. The bulky abdominal muscles that round the torso are called obliques. <br/><br/><b>The Confidence: A major determiner for the perfect look.</b> <br/>When we are confident, we believe we can do anything and have something to contribute. When it works well, it’s a bright, giving a sensation as opposed to a conceited, look-at-me emotion. With confidence, we can accomplish our goals without exerting too much effort. When individuals believe in their own abilities and appreciate themselves, they have a  sense of internal control. This is the power that comes with self- confidence. <br/><br/> When a confident person enters a room: head held high, solid handshake, friendly smile, and captivating eye contact, we connect with their comfortable speaking, smooth body language, and commanding demeanour.",
