    slug: "a-skin-care-routine-for-sensitive-skin",
    intro: "Do you have skin sensitivity issues? Sensitive skin is frequently inherited and can be affected by a wide range of things, including hormonal imbalances, a poor diet, climatic changes, and particular chemicals or components. To keep your sensitive skin quiet and clear, it's imperative to follow a regular skin care regimen. In order to help your skin behave, we've gathered some advice on how to treat your symptoms as well as a skin care regimen for sensitive skin.",
    content: "<b>Here's step by step sensitive skin care routine:</b><br/><br/>• Cleanse: Dermatologists advise using a gel or cream cleanser that gets rid of pollutants without irritating skin or making it too dry. Use your fingertips rather than a rag or brush to cleanse your face. Rinse with lukewarm water and gently pat your skin dry afterward. Above all, don't go overboard. It should be sufficient to wash your face once a day to maintain good skin. The skin is not overly stripped as the surplus filth and oil are gently removed by this gel cleanser. While chamomile and shea butter soothe and rehydrate dry skin, stone crop profoundly moisturises. <br/><br/>• Tone: A delicate and fresh complexion is revealed while using the hydrating Stone Crop Hydrating Mist, which is infused with stone crop juice and aloe. \"I spritz this on my face after cleansing and before I apply my bedtime moisturiser or midday sunscreen and LOVE it,\" writes Meredith in her 5-star review. My skin is rather delicate and easily irritated and itchy, but this always soothes, moisturises, and smooths it. It's incredible how much better my skin feels and looks after applying this mist. Without it, I can't live! You're welcome, Eminence. <br/><br/>• Moisturize: Look for moisturisers for sensitive skin that not only refill your skin's moisture barrier but also include calming elements that will ease and relax your skin. <br/><br/>This is how you can take care of your sensitive skin but in case you face any problem you should immediately contact to your dermatologist.",
